The article is a memorandum from President Barack Obama, addressing the unexpected urgent refugee and migration needs in the United States. The President determines that it is important to the national interest to provide assistance under the Migration and Refugee Assistance Act of 1962. An amount not exceeding $70 million will be allocated from the United States Emergency Refugee and Migration Assistance Fund to meet the urgent needs related to the U.S. Refugee Admissions Program. The funds will be used by the Department of State to address the increased number of refugees in need of resettlement. The memorandum concludes by authorizing and directing the publication of this memorandum in the Federal Register.